pylon - Change Log

================================================================================
Version 0.3.0 (2026-02-18) [UNRELEASED]
================================================================================

NEW FEATURES:
  * Added ~/.pylonrc config file support with INI-style sections
    - [cal] section: url
    - [discord] section: webhook, bot_token, guild_id, channel_id
  * Environment variables override config file values (PYLON_* takes precedence)
  * Config file is optional â€” env-only config still works

IMPROVEMENTS:
  * Load() now returns (*Config, error) for proper error propagation
  * Updated all usage/help text to document both config sources
  * Comprehensive test coverage for INI parser (sections, comments, whitespace,
    unknown keys, malformed lines, env override precedence)

================================================================================
Version 0.2.0 (2026-02-18) [UNRELEASED]
================================================================================

NEW FEATURES:
  * Discord service namespace (pylon discord ...):
    - msg: Send messages via webhook
    - read: Read recent messages from a channel (Bot API)
    - channels: List text channels in a guild (Bot API)
  * Config via env vars:
    - PYLON_DISCORD_WEBHOOK: Webhook URL for sending messages
    - PYLON_DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN: Bot token for reading messages/channels
    - PYLON_DISCORD_GUILD_ID: Default guild (server) ID
    - PYLON_DISCORD_CHANNEL_ID: Default channel ID for reading
  * Cal feed create now supports optional slug positional arg

================================================================================
Version 0.1.0 (2026-02-18)
================================================================================

NEW FEATURES:
  * Initial release of pylon CLI tool (renamed from xor)
  * Cal service integration:
    - feed create/list/delete: Manage calendar feeds
    - event add/list/delete: Manage calendar events
    - subscribe: Get webcal:// and https:// subscription URLs
  * HTTP client for cal service API with full error handling
  * Config via PYLON_CAL_URL env var (default http://localhost:8085)
  * --url flag override for per-command base URL
  * Tabwriter-formatted output for list commands

ARCHITECTURE:
  * Stdlib only - no external CLI framework
  * cmd/pylon/main.go: CLI entry point with subcommand routing
  * internal/cal/client.go: HTTP client for all cal API endpoints
  * internal/config/config.go: Environment-based configuration
  * Namespaced commands (pylon cal ...) designed for future service growth

TESTING:
  * Table-driven tests for all cal client methods (mock HTTP server)
  * Config package tests with env var isolation
  * 20 test cases covering success, error, and edge cases
